03:16.742 --> 03:18.911
20 bucks
to whoever finds it first.

03:30.189 --> 03:31.754
Found it.

03:31.756 --> 03:33.489
Looks like
you owe me some money.

03:35.560 --> 03:37.627
Listen, I'm gonna stay out here
and have a smoke,

03:37.629 --> 03:38.929
try not to go deaf.

03:38.931 --> 03:40.064
I hear that.

03:40.066 --> 03:41.464
Do your thing, man.

03:41.466 --> 03:42.701
All right.

03:58.683 --> 04:01.084
You fucking piece of...

04:01.086 --> 04:03.119
Hey!

04:45.863 --> 04:49.232
I'm prescribing GHB
to help manage your insomnia,

04:49.234 --> 04:51.134
but it is
a controlled substance, so...

04:51.136 --> 04:53.735
I won't need it.
I'm fine.

04:53.737 --> 04:56.838
Prolonged insomnia
will lead to confusion,

04:56.840 --> 04:58.507
delirium, hallucinations,

04:58.509 --> 05:00.042
and ultimately
dementia and death,

05:00.044 --> 05:03.214
so it's critical
you at least try to sleep.

05:05.649 --> 05:07.683
You're not gonna
fill that, are you?

05:07.685 --> 05:09.251
I don't think
you're taking to heart

05:09.253 --> 05:10.953
the seriousness
of this disease.

05:10.955 --> 05:12.287
It's the reason

05:12.289 --> 05:15.090
you're being released
from prison early.

05:19.997 --> 05:22.931
Just take these
until you see the specialist.

05:22.933 --> 05:25.233
If you don't sleep,
you will die.

05:25.235 --> 05:26.535
Do you hear
what I'm saying to you?

05:26.537 --> 05:27.736
Yes.

05:30.540 --> 05:31.773
Give this to your P.O.

05:31.775 --> 05:34.076
so he knows
the medication's cleared.

05:36.046 --> 05:37.611
Take care, Frank.

05:37.613 --> 05:39.216
Thanks, Doc.

08:05.160 --> 08:06.328
Joey?

08:17.105 --> 08:19.106
I figured
you wouldn't be here.

08:20.941 --> 08:22.344
Well, I'm here.

08:23.445 --> 08:25.177
Look at you.
You look...

08:25.179 --> 08:28.113
What? 19 years older than
the last time you saw me?

08:28.115 --> 08:31.083
Well, yeah.
You look like a man now.

08:31.085 --> 08:32.119
Because I am.

08:35.155 --> 08:37.722
- Let me get that for you.
- No, I can carry it.

08:37.725 --> 08:39.659
- Are you sure?
- Really, it's not that heavy.

08:40.895 --> 08:42.796
Fine.

08:43.964 --> 08:46.265
So I guess we're walking?

08:46.267 --> 08:48.066
Well, I had to sell the car
to pay off some stuff.

08:48.068 --> 08:50.402
- You know, bills and shit.
- I'm kidding.

08:50.404 --> 08:52.070
I don't mind walking.

08:52.072 --> 08:55.943
I don't normally get
a lot of time outside, so...

09:15.529 --> 09:17.929
You sure I can't
get you something to eat,

09:17.931 --> 09:21.433
compliments of the Grand Bend
Correctional Facility payroll?

09:21.435 --> 09:22.867
No. I'm good.

09:22.869 --> 09:24.436
You sure? I mean,
look how skinny you are.

09:24.438 --> 09:26.771
You look like you haven't
had a decent meal in months.

09:26.773 --> 09:27.805
What's that
supposed to mean?

09:27.807 --> 09:29.874
Nothing. I just...

09:29.876 --> 09:31.443
I mean, it's on me,
that's all.

09:31.445 --> 09:35.046
You know, a dad likes
to buy stuff for his kid.

09:35.048 --> 09:36.115
I didn't mean anything else.

09:41.854 --> 09:44.021
The coffee
tastes the same, but...

09:45.225 --> 09:48.125
...the air
sure smells different.

09:48.127 --> 09:51.095
And it's nice just to have
a normal pair of clothes on,

09:51.097 --> 09:52.230
you know?

09:52.232 --> 09:54.198
Even those?

09:54.200 --> 09:56.234
Well, I guess they are
kind of out of date, huh?

09:56.236 --> 09:57.568
I mean, 'cause that's
what you were wearing

09:57.570 --> 09:59.172
when they hauled you away.

10:07.313 --> 10:09.080
Take US 20 towards Salem,

10:09.082 --> 10:10.948
and I'll give you
directions from there.

10:10.950 --> 10:12.283
What the fuck you want
to go out there for?

10:12.285 --> 10:13.951
I just want to look
at the old house.

10:13.953 --> 10:16.053
Been a long time
since I've seen it.

10:16.055 --> 10:19.758
Fine.
Whatever you want.

10:34.340 --> 10:36.840
You know somebody else
lives there now.

10:36.842 --> 10:38.842
The family.

10:38.844 --> 10:40.912
I just want to take
a look around.

10:43.449 --> 10:45.248
I'm only gonna be a second.

10:45.250 --> 10:48.253
I just want to see if
something I left is still there.

13:26.276 --> 13:27.642
What the hell
took you so long?

13:27.644 --> 13:28.545
Oh...

13:32.515 --> 13:34.048
What happened to you?

13:34.050 --> 13:35.452
Nothing.

13:36.586 --> 13:38.319
Look what I found.

13:38.321 --> 13:41.055
- No shit.
- Unbelievable, right?

13:41.057 --> 13:42.223
It was like
my prized possession.

13:42.225 --> 13:43.591
Not that I would've known,

13:43.593 --> 13:45.493
the way you wouldn't let
anyone else touch it,

13:45.495 --> 13:48.028
and only held it yourself
with gloves on.

13:48.030 --> 13:50.063
Yeah, or, like, tweezers.

13:50.065 --> 13:51.265
Can't believe you found it.

13:51.267 --> 13:52.633
It's still
in amazing condition.

13:52.635 --> 13:55.470
- It is.
- Probably worth a lot.

13:55.472 --> 13:56.639
Yeah.

13:57.774 --> 13:59.674
Wonder what
I could sell it for.

13:59.676 --> 14:02.042
I mean, it's got to be
a collector's item, right?

14:02.044 --> 14:04.545
Please, don't sell it.

14:04.547 --> 14:06.112
If you don't want it,

14:06.114 --> 14:08.114
I'd like to keep it,
if you don't mind.

14:08.116 --> 14:10.551
I'll give you the money for it,
if you want.

14:10.553 --> 14:11.688
Okay.

14:14.757 --> 14:16.156
So where to now?

14:16.158 --> 14:17.692
Well...

14:17.694 --> 14:20.327
You and I
are gonna live it up.

15:37.405 --> 15:38.905
What are we doing here?

15:38.907 --> 15:40.807
Meeting my parole officer.

15:42.577 --> 15:44.643
We're checking in!

15:44.645 --> 15:47.348
Compliments of
the prison payroll?

15:48.549 --> 15:50.616
After a $300 cab ride,
I don't think so.

15:50.618 --> 15:51.850
I got it covered.

15:51.852 --> 15:53.387
Keep the change.

15:56.424 --> 15:58.324
You're using their money,
aren't you?

15:58.326 --> 15:59.792
After everything
they did to you?

15:59.794 --> 16:01.293
After everything they did
to us?

16:01.295 --> 16:03.862
Hell, yes,
after everything they did to us.

16:03.864 --> 16:05.397
After everything
they did to us,

16:05.399 --> 16:07.433
I'm gonna use
every last dollar.

16:07.435 --> 16:08.934
That's the least
they owe us.

16:08.936 --> 16:09.835
Okay.

16:09.837 --> 16:11.437
Well, knock yourself out.

16:11.439 --> 16:12.638
I don't want
any part of it.

16:12.640 --> 16:14.640
Joey! No.
Joey, don't go, please.

16:14.642 --> 16:16.775
Look, I want
to show you something.

16:16.777 --> 16:17.843
Look at this.

16:17.845 --> 16:19.411
Your mother brought me here

16:19.413 --> 16:21.780
as a surprise
for our second anniversary,

16:21.782 --> 16:23.247
and I was pissed

16:23.249 --> 16:24.550
because we didn't have
a dime between us

16:24.552 --> 16:26.250
but she said
none of that mattered,

16:26.252 --> 16:28.887
we can work out anything
as long as we're together.

16:28.889 --> 16:31.557
And I always wanted
to bring her back here, but I...

16:31.559 --> 16:33.358
I didn't get
around to it, did I?

16:33.360 --> 16:35.393
But the only thing
I thought about

16:35.395 --> 16:38.496
for every minute of every day
since I got locked up

16:38.498 --> 16:40.231
was how much I wanted
to bring you here.

16:40.233 --> 16:42.801
So please... please stay.

16:42.803 --> 16:45.238
You're all I got left.

16:48.876 --> 16:50.742
- Fine.
- All right.

16:50.744 --> 16:52.278
All right.

16:54.882 --> 16:56.949
That's for you.

16:56.951 --> 16:58.418
For you.

17:09.695 --> 17:12.198
Thanks.
We'll take it from here.

17:13.633 --> 17:15.335
Hey, hey.

17:16.636 --> 17:19.303
Nice!

17:19.305 --> 17:20.538
This is a step up

17:20.540 --> 17:22.942
from my previous
accommodations, right?

17:26.980 --> 17:31.381
Joey!
Six shower heads!

17:31.383 --> 17:33.887
It's our own personal spa.

17:37.389 --> 17:39.256
We're well stocked.

17:39.258 --> 17:40.758
Want a drink?

17:40.760 --> 17:42.261
No, I'm good.

17:47.934 --> 17:50.434
Oh!

17:50.436 --> 17:52.904
Oh, my God.

17:52.906 --> 17:55.505
Oh, you have no idea how hard
prison mattresses are.

17:55.507 --> 17:56.974
I don't even think

17:56.976 --> 17:59.409
they're stuffed with cotton
or whatever, just rocks.

17:59.411 --> 18:01.745
Come on. Lie down.
You got to feel this.

18:01.747 --> 18:03.749
- I'm good.
- Come on!

18:08.054 --> 18:09.521
Joey!

18:12.458 --> 18:14.691
Well, I'm gonna
take a shower,

18:14.693 --> 18:16.827
and then let's
grab some dinner.

18:16.829 --> 18:19.830
What do you think?
Does that sound good?

18:19.832 --> 18:21.233
Joey?

19:15.453 --> 19:17.520
Now, Joey,

19:17.522 --> 19:19.789
I want you to order
whatever you want.

19:19.791 --> 19:21.757
Spare no expense.

19:21.759 --> 19:24.760
I am treating you
to the best week of your life.

19:24.762 --> 19:27.363
- Dad...
- Whatever you want, you got it.

19:27.365 --> 19:29.632
It all looks so good.

19:29.634 --> 19:31.834
So get two things.
Get three!

19:31.836 --> 19:33.702
I'm not sure
I'm all that hungry.

19:33.704 --> 19:36.038
How can you not be hungry?

19:36.040 --> 19:37.642
You haven't eaten all day.

19:40.044 --> 19:41.510
I just meant...

19:41.512 --> 19:43.445
You know I've never
been a big eater.

19:43.447 --> 19:44.680
- I know.
- Even when I was a kid.

19:44.682 --> 19:46.381
I know.

19:46.383 --> 19:48.383
For your information,
I've been clean for a while now.

19:48.385 --> 19:49.954
I didn't mean anything by it.

19:52.389 --> 19:54.455
So catch me up on your life.

19:54.457 --> 19:56.058
I want to know everything
that's been going on.

19:56.060 --> 19:57.793
You got a girl?

19:57.795 --> 19:59.762
You know, it's kind of hard
to sum up 19 years

19:59.764 --> 20:02.597
in one dinner conversation.

20:02.599 --> 20:04.066
Where are you going?

20:04.068 --> 20:05.533
Bathroom.
Just order me whatever.

20:05.535 --> 20:07.535
- I upset you. I'm sorry.
- No, I'm not upset!

20:07.537 --> 20:10.705
I have to piss.
That okay with you?

20:10.707 --> 20:12.774
Joey.

20:12.776 --> 20:14.977
Come on.
Sit with your old man!

20:43.640 --> 20:45.942
Thank you.

20:48.912 --> 20:50.647
Thank you.

20:51.915 --> 20:53.548
I love this place.

20:53.550 --> 20:55.550
It's very nice.

20:55.552 --> 20:58.620
How've you been?
I've been really well.

20:58.622 --> 21:00.021
- It's good to see you.
- You too.

21:00.023 --> 21:01.956
Guy's old enough
to be her grandfather.

21:01.958 --> 21:03.591
What took you so long?

21:03.593 --> 21:05.159
Looks even older than you.

21:05.161 --> 21:07.695
See?
There's hope for me yet.

21:07.697 --> 21:10.098
Yeah, if you got
two G's to burn.

21:10.100 --> 21:11.465
What?
You think she's...

21:11.467 --> 21:13.835
- A prostitute, yeah.
- Come on!

21:13.837 --> 21:18.806
Just saying.
Times have changed, old man.

21:20.542 --> 21:22.778
How many times
have you been there?

21:28.084 --> 21:30.918
I don't know why I didn't
bring any clothes with me.

21:30.920 --> 21:32.853
We'll go shopping
for some tomorrow.

21:32.855 --> 21:34.057
Okay.

21:35.557 --> 21:37.191
I just want to say good night.

21:37.193 --> 21:39.059
Good night.

21:39.061 --> 21:41.628
Hey.
Um...

21:41.630 --> 21:43.666
Can I show you something?

21:48.504 --> 21:49.672
I hope you like it.

21:54.944 --> 21:56.877
Solid maple.

21:56.879 --> 21:58.278
I made over 40 of them.

21:58.280 --> 21:59.780
- You made them?
- Yeah.

21:59.782 --> 22:01.248
And I actually had
orders come in

22:01.250 --> 22:04.518
from all over the country
at one time.

22:04.520 --> 22:06.720
I ended up coaching inside,

22:06.722 --> 22:08.021
and it reminded me

22:08.023 --> 22:09.656
of when you used to play
Little League

22:09.658 --> 22:12.558
and I'd help out
every now and again.

22:12.560 --> 22:14.995
I wish I had made more time
for it back then.

22:14.997 --> 22:17.164
I hated playing, anyways.

22:17.166 --> 22:19.733
No, you didn't.
You loved it.

22:19.735 --> 22:21.667
You were good at it, too.

22:21.669 --> 22:24.139
You could've made it
to the big leagues.

22:37.719 --> 22:39.821
That's not
how I remember it.

22:43.024 --> 22:46.161
Yeah, you could've,
if you'd stuck with it.

22:50.698 --> 22:52.131
Well, did you make
this one too?

22:52.133 --> 22:56.804
No. That's birch.
Not nearly as good as maple.

23:00.008 --> 23:02.274
I know I was never any good
at the whole father thing.

23:02.276 --> 23:04.110
- Dad, don't.
- No. It's true.

23:04.112 --> 23:06.879
I stank as a dad,
but I'm gonna make it up to you

23:06.881 --> 23:09.148
for being gone
when you really needed me.

23:09.150 --> 23:11.152
Yeah, like my entire life.

23:18.860 --> 23:20.693
Are you planning
on getting revenge?

23:20.695 --> 23:22.697
What? No.

23:23.898 --> 23:25.233
Really?

23:26.901 --> 23:29.701
I'm done with those people.

23:29.703 --> 23:31.303
I'm done with all of it.

23:31.305 --> 23:32.704
I'm just making sure

23:32.706 --> 23:34.639
I get you and me right
this time.

23:34.641 --> 23:37.711
You're stuck with me,
whether you like it or not.

23:39.746 --> 23:43.017
And I'm never
leaving you again.

24:36.169 --> 24:38.002
Where do you think
you're going, Pops?

24:38.004 --> 24:39.871
I'm looking for Sleepy.
I'm a friend.

24:39.873 --> 24:41.272
I think you're in
the wrong place.

24:41.274 --> 24:43.774
I don't know who the fuck
you're talking about.

24:43.776 --> 24:46.277
- That's a 226 clone.
- Yeah.

24:46.279 --> 24:48.712
You want to see it up close?
Want to suck on it?

24:48.714 --> 24:50.781
You kids like them because
you think they look cool.

24:50.783 --> 24:52.150
Truth is, it's one of

24:52.152 --> 24:53.951
the most unreliable firearms
in the world.

24:53.953 --> 24:55.819
Sights are crude,
weight's all wrong,

24:55.821 --> 24:57.288
the design's
entirely impractical,

24:57.290 --> 24:59.457
and if you don't have
just the right ammunition,

24:59.459 --> 25:00.791
it's guaranteed
to jam up on you.

25:00.793 --> 25:02.227
Come on, kid, take it easy.

25:02.229 --> 25:04.295
I'm just here to do
some business with Sleepy.

25:04.297 --> 25:09.233
Sleepy's been
dead for six years.

25:09.235 --> 25:12.271
Doesn't change
what I'm bringing to the table.

25:14.441 --> 25:16.206
So you're in charge now?

25:16.208 --> 25:19.211
Why are you asking?
'Cause I don't got a dick?

25:20.346 --> 25:23.847
The world's changed
since your day, old man.

25:23.849 --> 25:26.750
So you used to do business
with Sleepy?

25:26.752 --> 25:28.485
How'd he die?

25:28.487 --> 25:30.787
Old bastard
smoked all the time.

25:30.789 --> 25:33.290
Even burned me
when I was a baby.

25:33.292 --> 25:35.092
Accidentally.

25:35.094 --> 25:36.727
Shit.
You're Sleepy's kid?

25:36.729 --> 25:38.862
You were always
running around here,

25:38.864 --> 25:39.997
getting into things.

25:39.999 --> 25:41.999
Fuck it.

25:42.001 --> 25:43.903
Let's get you a gun, yeah?

25:50.509 --> 25:53.245
Got some mad recoil,
you know.

25:54.246 --> 25:57.181
I'll take it. And a suppressor
if you've got one.

25:57.183 --> 25:58.417
I do.

26:01.786 --> 26:02.885
And a 9-millimeter.

26:02.887 --> 26:04.190
Something Italian.

26:20.171 --> 26:23.208
- Who's this?
- That's my little man, Isaiah.

26:25.343 --> 26:28.411
I guess everything
comes full circle.

26:28.413 --> 26:29.812
Yeah.

26:29.814 --> 26:31.849
Do you mind
if I give him something?

26:36.821 --> 26:38.888
I made these myself.

26:38.890 --> 26:41.524
My son's too old
to play with them,

26:41.526 --> 26:44.460
so maybe someday
you'll play.

26:44.462 --> 26:46.128
So you getting back
in the racket again?

26:46.130 --> 26:47.330
That's why
you're back in town?

26:47.332 --> 26:50.802
Just dropping in
on some old friends.

27:04.148 --> 27:06.017
Sorry. We're closed.

27:09.153 --> 27:11.356
Hey, I said we're closed.

27:12.990 --> 27:15.424
San Quentin.

27:15.426 --> 27:17.426
Frankie Fingers.

27:17.428 --> 27:20.128
I just go by Frank now.

27:20.130 --> 27:23.800
People just call me Q now.

27:27.572 --> 27:29.538
You son of a bitch!
Is that really you?

27:29.540 --> 27:33.010
Come here, man!

27:33.844 --> 27:35.478
Oh, they finally
let you out, huh?

27:35.480 --> 27:38.380
They do that sometimes
with frail old men like me.

27:38.382 --> 27:40.081
Yeah, well,
little do they know.

27:40.083 --> 27:42.017
Oh, we could write a book
about how little they know.

27:42.019 --> 27:43.151
Hey, do you still drink whiskey?

27:43.153 --> 27:44.953
Yeah.
Flies still eat shit?

27:44.955 --> 27:47.389
Well, it looks like
you've been doing well.

27:47.391 --> 27:50.560
Uh, yeah, you know,
uh, not bad.

27:52.462 --> 27:54.296
How'd they treat you
in there, Frankie?

27:54.298 --> 27:57.365
You wound up spending
a lot more time in there

