48:12.798 --> 48:15.365
Oh, shit.
I broke your heart.

48:15.367 --> 48:17.167
What? No.
Not possible!

48:17.169 --> 48:18.602
It's made of cast iron.
See?

48:18.604 --> 48:20.170
Ah!

48:20.172 --> 48:23.473
Anyway, I'll, uh,
call your service tomorrow,

48:23.475 --> 48:25.275
and maybe we can have
some dinner,

48:25.277 --> 48:26.776
so I can make it up to you.

48:26.778 --> 48:28.077
Make what up to me?

48:28.079 --> 48:30.145
Me being a stupid old man.

48:31.215 --> 48:33.617
All right. Dinner.

48:33.619 --> 48:35.150
Tomorrow.

48:35.152 --> 48:37.721
Call the service.
You got the number.

48:37.723 --> 48:39.056
- I do.
- Okay.

48:40.626 --> 48:41.858
Hey, e-excuse me.

48:43.194 --> 48:44.796
Is Simone really your name?

48:46.465 --> 48:48.097
No.

48:48.099 --> 48:49.500
It's Jennifer.

49:57.200 --> 50:00.705
Hey, baby. You want to
play with the Dragon?

50:14.484 --> 50:17.552
I had no idea
this was your scene, Jimmy.

50:17.554 --> 50:19.387
It's the 21st century,
Frankie.

50:19.389 --> 50:21.623
A man can pamper himself.

50:21.625 --> 50:23.426
Indulge.

50:24.361 --> 50:25.528
Bitches, leave.

50:29.232 --> 50:33.201
Not nice to deprive a guy
of his happy ending.

50:33.203 --> 50:35.970
Prison life agreed with you.
You look fit.

50:35.972 --> 50:38.239
You dropped
a couple of pounds, I see.

50:38.241 --> 50:39.240
Cover up.

50:39.242 --> 50:40.608
What?

50:40.610 --> 50:42.243
Oh.

50:42.245 --> 50:44.946
Is that making you
uncomfortable?

50:44.948 --> 50:46.981
I can understand why.

50:46.983 --> 50:51.352
They don't call me the Dragon
because of my tattoo.

50:51.354 --> 50:53.888
Ah, you're a pretty smug
piece of shit

50:53.890 --> 50:56.457
for a guy who's got
a gun pointed at his head.

50:56.459 --> 50:57.592
It's not the first time.

50:57.594 --> 50:59.460
Probably won't be the last.

50:59.462 --> 51:00.828
Oh, it's your last.

51:00.830 --> 51:03.365
But you're gonna
explain something to me first.

51:04.366 --> 51:05.602
Then you might as well
shoot me.

51:07.737 --> 51:09.839
Because I haven't a clue
where Max has been hiding.

51:11.775 --> 51:12.842
Max...

51:14.778 --> 51:16.645
...is alive?

51:17.914 --> 51:20.447
Oh, shit.

51:54.917 --> 51:56.719
Just like the old days,
baby!

51:57.720 --> 51:59.220
Where do you think
you're going?

52:14.636 --> 52:16.772
Sorry, Frankie.
Nothing personal.

52:32.420 --> 52:34.320
Finally!

52:34.322 --> 52:36.390
You know how long I've been
waiting for you, young man?

52:39.827 --> 52:43.297
Thought you guys might've
ran off to Vegas to get married.

52:46.834 --> 52:49.435
So how was she?

52:49.437 --> 52:50.838
Was she incredible?

52:52.840 --> 52:54.006
You guys sleep at all,

52:54.008 --> 52:56.776
or you just at it
the whole time?

52:56.778 --> 52:58.110
Oh, nice.

52:58.112 --> 53:00.713
Your doctor gave you
the good stuff, huh?

53:06.487 --> 53:07.720
You gonna tell me anything?

53:07.722 --> 53:09.655
Can't talk
about it right now.

53:09.657 --> 53:10.990
Come on!

53:10.992 --> 53:12.525
First time you make mercury
in 19 years,

53:12.527 --> 53:13.993
and I don't get anything?

53:13.995 --> 53:15.730
Was she loud?

53:17.832 --> 53:18.933
What the hell
happened to you?

53:20.433 --> 53:23.736
Dad! What the hell
happened to you?

53:23.738 --> 53:25.638
- Answer me!
- What do you think happened?

53:25.640 --> 53:27.605
I met up with Jimmy the Dragon
and we had it out!

53:27.607 --> 53:29.607
- You killed him?
- Sadly, no.

53:29.609 --> 53:31.043
What the fuck?
You hid an arsenal in here

53:31.045 --> 53:32.410
the whole fucking time?

53:32.412 --> 53:33.745
You said you were
done with them!

53:33.747 --> 53:35.480
You said you weren't
looking to get even!

53:35.482 --> 53:37.715
Scores have to be settled.

53:37.717 --> 53:39.386
Says who?!

53:40.487 --> 53:41.887
You're a big fucking liar!

53:41.889 --> 53:44.023
- I'm doing this for you!
- That's bullshit!

53:44.025 --> 53:45.890
I am doing this for you!
Everything I do is for you!

53:45.892 --> 53:47.759
Oh, so it's all on me, huh?

53:47.761 --> 53:49.894
You getting locked up for two
fucking decades, that's on me?

53:49.896 --> 53:50.895
Yes!

53:50.897 --> 53:52.164
Because every penny I made,

53:52.166 --> 53:53.598
you took and you snorted
it up your nose

53:53.600 --> 53:55.500
and you shot it
in your veins!

53:55.502 --> 53:57.502
Oh, what?
Am I out of order?

53:57.504 --> 53:59.539
You think I'm fucking
using right now?

54:00.774 --> 54:02.073
Do you?

54:02.075 --> 54:03.508
Take a fucking look!

54:03.510 --> 54:06.110
Take a good fucking look!
All right?

54:06.112 --> 54:08.913
You satisfied, Detective?

54:08.915 --> 54:11.916
I don't understand why you care
all of a sudden.

54:11.918 --> 54:13.918
<i>Now</i> you want to teach me
right from wrong?

54:13.920 --> 54:16.588
Like you're my father?

54:16.590 --> 54:18.890
Like you're some shining
fucking example?

54:18.892 --> 54:20.692
- You better walk away.
- What are you gonna do?

54:20.694 --> 54:22.660
You're gonna knock me out?

54:22.662 --> 54:24.494
Huh?

54:24.496 --> 54:26.496
You know, why don't you reach
into that big black bag of yours

54:26.498 --> 54:27.531
and do it right?

54:27.533 --> 54:29.736
How about that, Dad?

54:31.437 --> 54:32.937
I got to go.

54:32.939 --> 54:34.939
You can lie to yourself
all you want,

54:34.941 --> 54:36.040
but I'm done with it!

54:36.042 --> 54:37.507
You hear me?

54:37.509 --> 54:38.977
You walk out that door
and I'm gone!

54:38.979 --> 54:40.444
That's it!

54:40.446 --> 54:43.049
You're never gonna
see me again.

56:03.828 --> 56:05.496
Frankie.

56:07.665 --> 56:09.099
Hiya, Tank.

56:09.101 --> 56:11.736
"Tank."

56:12.937 --> 56:16.005
Man, no one's called me that
in a long time.

56:17.675 --> 56:19.644
I heard you got out.

56:21.579 --> 56:23.715
I figured you'd come
looking for me.

56:27.618 --> 56:30.119
How you doing?

56:30.121 --> 56:32.088
Not too bad.

56:32.090 --> 56:34.692
- You?
- Can't complain.

56:36.094 --> 56:38.728
I mean, I've been having
some troubles with my hands

56:38.730 --> 56:40.830
a little bit.

56:40.832 --> 56:43.132
I think I may be
getting some arthritis.

56:43.134 --> 56:45.101
- That sucks.
- Ah, it happens.

56:45.103 --> 56:48.004
Makes working
kind of difficult.

56:48.006 --> 56:50.638
Never figured you the type
for legitimate work.

56:50.640 --> 56:52.208
Got to stay busy somehow,
right?

56:52.210 --> 56:54.912
It's not like I got a family
or anything. It's just me.

56:57.714 --> 57:00.782
Life never really turns out
the way you plan it.

57:00.784 --> 57:04.120
No. It doesn't.

57:04.122 --> 57:06.654
Anyway...

57:06.656 --> 57:10.192
You got to do
what you came here for, so...

57:10.194 --> 57:13.264
You're not gonna run?
Put up a fight?

57:14.232 --> 57:17.233
I figure I've outrun
what I got coming to me

57:17.235 --> 57:19.034
way longer
than I deserve.

57:19.036 --> 57:21.104
One thing first,
if you don't mind.

57:22.973 --> 57:24.939
Do you know
where I can find Max?

57:24.941 --> 57:27.142
I don't.

57:27.144 --> 57:30.379
Last time I saw him
was before he had his stroke.

57:30.381 --> 57:36.785
So you don't know anything
about him faking his death?

57:36.787 --> 57:39.654
Well, actually,
I did hear something.

57:39.656 --> 57:41.823
I heard a few guys
talking about that,

57:41.825 --> 57:45.160
but I wasn't sure
if it wasn't just talk.

57:45.162 --> 57:47.097
I wish I could help you.

57:48.198 --> 57:50.767
I mean, I know I owe you.

57:53.904 --> 57:55.136
Wait. Do you know...
You know what?

57:55.138 --> 57:56.905
I don't know, I'm not sure,
but may...

57:56.907 --> 57:58.740
maybe I did
hear something about his kid

57:58.742 --> 58:01.078
dumping him in
an old-folk home a while back.

58:02.312 --> 58:04.047
Thank you.

58:09.685 --> 58:12.588
Frankie, Frankie, Frankie.
Frankie.

58:14.690 --> 58:17.825
Hey, look,
I'm really sorry, man.

58:17.827 --> 58:19.329
About everything.

58:55.397 --> 58:56.697
Let's see here.

59:01.403 --> 59:04.238
♪ I am ♪

59:04.240 --> 59:05.973
♪ Always ♪

59:05.975 --> 59:09.775
♪ Chasing rainbows ♪

59:09.777 --> 59:11.879
♪ Watching clouds ♪

59:11.881 --> 59:13.813
♪ Drifting by ♪

59:13.815 --> 59:15.282
♪ Ooh ♪

59:15.284 --> 59:20.820
♪ My schemes
are just like all my dreams ♪

59:20.822 --> 59:22.788
♪ Ending in ♪

59:22.790 --> 59:25.791
♪ The sky ♪

59:25.793 --> 59:28.794
♪ Some fellas look
and find the sunshine ♪

59:28.796 --> 59:31.465
♪ I always look
and find the rain ♪

59:31.467 --> 59:34.100
You danced to that song
with Lorraine at your wedding.

59:34.102 --> 59:36.969
She thought
it was a happy song.

59:36.971 --> 59:38.838
What the hell
happened to you?

59:38.840 --> 59:40.940
♪ I was just taking care
of loose ends ♪

59:40.942 --> 59:43.009
Frank.
Frank, Frank, Frank, look.

59:43.011 --> 59:44.810
All of the guys
that we came up with

59:44.812 --> 59:46.946
that didn't get killed,
they all smartened up enough

59:46.948 --> 59:48.281
to know when
it was time to get out.

59:48.283 --> 59:50.183
That game of "gang" shit
that we used to play

59:50.185 --> 59:51.418
is for kids.

59:51.420 --> 59:53.419
Okay?
And we are not kids anymore.

59:53.421 --> 59:55.388
♪ I'm not playing anymore
either ♪

59:55.390 --> 59:56.889
♪ Believe me ♪

59:56.891 --> 59:58.958
They deserve what
they got coming, okay?

59:58.960 --> 01:00:00.359
No question about it.

01:00:00.361 --> 01:00:02.929
- ♪ Chasing rainbows ♪
- But, fuck, hey.

01:00:02.931 --> 01:00:04.130
Is it really worth it?

01:00:04.132 --> 01:00:05.831
Is it going
to change anything?

01:00:05.833 --> 01:00:07.066
♪ Waiting to find ♪

01:00:07.068 --> 01:00:09.435
♪ A little bluebird ♪

01:00:09.437 --> 01:00:10.970
It'll change the fact

01:00:10.972 --> 01:00:12.805
that I'm the only one
that got screwed.

01:00:12.807 --> 01:00:14.173
And what if
you get killed first?

01:00:14.175 --> 01:00:16.275
I mean, look at the state
of you already, man.

01:00:16.277 --> 01:00:18.044
People are
gonna die either way.

01:00:18.046 --> 01:00:19.178
No way around it.

01:00:19.180 --> 01:00:23.182
Just a matter of
who goes next.

01:00:25.053 --> 01:00:28.020
We hurt a lot of people,
you and I.

01:00:28.022 --> 01:00:30.789
Made a lot of bad choices
that now we just

01:00:30.791 --> 01:00:33.359
need to learn to live with.

01:00:33.361 --> 01:00:35.860
Look, why don't you come
to Isha's wedding tomorrow?

01:00:35.862 --> 01:00:38.029
Be a part of some real-life
shit. It'll be good for you.

01:00:38.031 --> 01:00:41.132
You can even bring somebody,
okay? A date.

01:00:41.134 --> 01:00:42.867
Maybe you'll even meet
a nice woman there.

01:00:42.869 --> 01:00:44.869
I don't know.

01:00:44.871 --> 01:00:46.372
Well, think about it.

01:00:46.374 --> 01:00:49.040
We'd love to have you.

01:00:49.042 --> 01:00:50.744
You're family.

01:00:51.945 --> 01:00:53.981
Yeah, maybe.

01:01:40.893 --> 01:01:42.095
Joey?

01:01:43.863 --> 01:01:45.265
Hey, Joey?

01:01:51.571 --> 01:01:54.472
Oh.
Sorry.

01:01:54.474 --> 01:01:57.377
No, it's okay.
Just do your work.

01:02:50.129 --> 01:02:52.298
<i>¿Habla Inglés?</i>

01:03:12.485 --> 01:03:13.950
Uh, hey,

01:03:13.952 --> 01:03:16.052
kid, can you help me
with something?

01:03:16.054 --> 01:03:17.255
Of course, sir.

01:03:25.130 --> 01:03:27.063
I have to call my son,

01:03:27.065 --> 01:03:31.134
and I have no idea how
to work this damn thing.

01:03:31.136 --> 01:03:35.238
Well, uh, I can certainly
help you with that, Mister...?

01:03:35.240 --> 01:03:38.207
- Carver.
- Mr. Carver.

01:03:38.209 --> 01:03:41.577
See, I just find
your address book app.

01:03:41.579 --> 01:03:43.980
Uh, what is your son's name?

01:03:43.982 --> 01:03:45.715
Uh, Joey. Joseph.

01:03:45.717 --> 01:03:48.985
It's, uh... It's empty.

01:03:48.987 --> 01:03:52.321
Oh, yeah. I just
got the thing yesterday.

01:03:52.323 --> 01:03:55.023
Well, has he called you
since, or...

01:03:55.025 --> 01:03:57.660
He, uh, um,

01:03:57.662 --> 01:03:59.529
"face-called" me
yesterday.

01:03:59.531 --> 01:04:00.996
Uh, great.

01:04:00.998 --> 01:04:02.265
So, um,

01:04:02.267 --> 01:04:04.300
I just find the phone app...

01:04:04.302 --> 01:04:05.501
Uh-huh.

01:04:05.503 --> 01:04:07.303
...and go
to your call history.

01:04:07.305 --> 01:04:09.273
- Oh.
- Here. And...

01:04:10.675 --> 01:04:12.475
Yeah, that's empty, too.

01:04:12.477 --> 01:04:14.477
Aw, shit.
Really?

01:04:14.479 --> 01:04:17.780
Maybe you accidentally
cleared it, or...?

01:04:17.782 --> 01:04:20.483
I wouldn't put it past me.

01:04:20.485 --> 01:04:22.350
Is there any way
you can get it back?

01:04:22.352 --> 01:04:24.152
I'm awfully sorry, sir.

01:04:24.154 --> 01:04:26.421
Oh, that's okay.

01:04:26.423 --> 01:04:28.658
Thank you.

01:04:28.660 --> 01:04:31.259
Uh, hey, but you can...

01:04:31.261 --> 01:04:33.628
you can use this thing
to get on the Web, right?

01:04:33.630 --> 01:04:35.096
Most definitely, sir.

01:04:35.098 --> 01:04:37.499
Okay, well, then,
can you look up

01:04:37.501 --> 01:04:40.235
all the nursing homes
in the area...

01:04:40.237 --> 01:04:42.070
no, in the state, actually...

01:04:42.072 --> 01:04:44.239
a-and write me up
a list and...

01:04:44.241 --> 01:04:45.740
Mr. Carver, I can't...

01:04:45.742 --> 01:04:47.478
I'll give you $500.

01:04:49.746 --> 01:04:51.746
L-Let me grab a pad, yeah.

01:04:51.748 --> 01:04:54.151
Good man.

01:05:17.808 --> 01:05:20.042
I'm dying.

01:05:23.847 --> 01:05:27.381
They told me I had

01:05:27.383 --> 01:05:31.120
fatal sporadic insomnia.

01:05:32.355 --> 01:05:34.188
I can't sleep.

01:05:34.190 --> 01:05:36.825
There's something wrong
with my brain.

01:05:36.827 --> 01:05:41.464
It's incurable.

01:05:43.566 --> 01:05:47.603
And untreatable.

01:05:50.239 --> 01:05:52.506
God, I'm...

01:05:52.508 --> 01:05:54.308
I'm sorry, sir.

01:05:54.310 --> 01:05:57.578
Well, at least
I get to take

01:05:57.580 --> 01:05:59.782
a few of them
down with me, right?

01:06:03.853 --> 01:06:06.322
Joey?

01:06:08.157 --> 01:06:10.124
Joey, is that you?

01:06:10.126 --> 01:06:11.292
It's Simone!

01:06:11.294 --> 01:06:13.661
Oh, shit.

01:06:13.663 --> 01:06:16.198
Simone.
Oh, shit.

01:06:25.474 --> 01:06:27.140
Ah!

01:06:27.142 --> 01:06:30.878
Simone!
I'm sorry, honey.

01:06:30.880 --> 01:06:35.148
I forgot about
our dinner plans.

01:06:42.223 --> 01:06:44.725
Hi, sweetie.

01:06:44.727 --> 01:06:46.526
Who are you?

01:06:46.528 --> 01:06:49.930
I'm Simone, baby.
You called me for a date?

01:06:49.932 --> 01:06:53.366
Y-You're not Simone.

01:06:53.368 --> 01:06:57.505
I assure you, honey, I am.

01:06:58.440 --> 01:07:01.307
Mm. You gonna fix me
a drink, or what?

01:07:01.309 --> 01:07:05.411
There's been a mistake.
I called for the other Simone.

01:07:05.413 --> 01:07:08.281
She's this tall,
has dark hair.

01:07:08.283 --> 01:07:09.782
Real name's Jennifer.

01:07:09.784 --> 01:07:11.784
I don't know, baby.
I guess she couldn't make it.

01:07:11.786 --> 01:07:13.386
Hi, cutie.

01:07:13.388 --> 01:07:15.254
It's gonna cost you extra
if he's watching.

01:07:15.256 --> 01:07:16.689
Why?

01:07:16.691 --> 01:07:18.691
Why can't she make it?

01:07:18.693 --> 01:07:23.396
Why are you so stuck
on this other girl, sweetie?

01:07:23.398 --> 01:07:25.832
I'm right here,
and she's not.

01:07:25.834 --> 01:07:28.768
Well, you see, <i>sweetie,</i>

01:07:28.770 --> 01:07:30.637
you're not the girl
I called for,

01:07:30.639 --> 01:07:32.204
so you're gonna
have to leave.

01:07:32.206 --> 01:07:33.673
I'm not fucking you.

01:07:33.675 --> 01:07:35.942
Get your fucking meat paws
off me, you ugly fuck!

01:07:35.944 --> 01:07:39.648
Shut the fuck up and get out,
you phony piece of shit.

01:07:49.891 --> 01:07:53.293
Jesus Christ.
Now what?

01:07:55.629 --> 01:07:56.829
Hello?

01:07:56.831 --> 01:07:57.964
Hey, Frank.

01:07:57.966 --> 01:07:59.598
Yeah?

01:07:59.600 --> 01:08:00.634
It's Trip.

01:08:01.702 --> 01:08:04.436
Aw, come on, don't tell me
you don't remember me.

01:08:04.438 --> 01:08:06.271
From the other day?

01:08:06.273 --> 01:08:08.007
"Expensive car,
expensive suit..."

01:08:08.009 --> 01:08:09.675
Yeah, I remember you.

01:08:09.677 --> 01:08:11.810
So the Presidential Suite, huh?

01:08:11.812 --> 01:08:13.845
How much you have to pay
for a room like that,

01:08:13.847 --> 01:08:14.946
if you don't mind me asking?

01:08:14.948 --> 01:08:16.782
Actually, I do mind.

01:08:17.885 --> 01:08:19.653
That's me.

01:08:28.662 --> 01:08:30.895
Hi, Frank.
Got a minute?

01:08:30.898 --> 01:08:31.997
No.

01:08:31.999 --> 01:08:33.698
Ooh.

01:08:33.701 --> 01:08:35.033
Oh, yeah!

01:08:35.035 --> 01:08:37.803
Look at this place, huh?

01:08:37.805 --> 01:08:40.206
Fucking top tier!

01:08:40.941 --> 01:08:43.608
I hope I can afford
a room like this one day.

01:08:43.609 --> 01:08:46.678
Maybe if I just keep my nose
to the grindstone,

01:08:46.680 --> 01:08:48.613
work hard.

01:08:48.615 --> 01:08:51.049
What do you think, Frank?
You think it'll happen for me?

01:08:51.051 --> 01:08:52.517
Are you gonna whimper
all night,

01:08:52.519 --> 01:08:54.417
or is there something
you want from me?

01:08:54.420 --> 01:08:56.921
I hear you had a little bit of
a problem with one of my girls.

01:08:56.924 --> 01:08:59.024
She wasn't the girl
I called for.

01:08:59.026 --> 01:09:00.357
I called for Simone.

01:09:00.359 --> 01:09:01.727
Yeah, well,
Simone was busy.

01:09:01.729 --> 01:09:03.694
Besides,
you scared the bitch.

01:09:03.697 --> 01:09:05.429
She's afraid of you, Frank.

01:09:05.430 --> 01:09:07.631
